The paper focuses on using natural language processing techniques to extract disease data from Wikipedia articles. This falls under the sub-category of information retrieval (cs.IR) as the authors are retrieving relevant information from unstructured text. Additionally, the paper involves training a named-entity recognizer, which falls under the sub-category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The use of internet-based disease surveillance systems also involves social media analysis and network analysis, which could fall under the sub-categories of social and information networks (cs.SI), cybernetics (cs.CY), and systems and control (cs.SD).
